docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, Nov. 5 -- Japan has transferred its wool buying from Australia to Argentina and Uruguay as part of its campaign of reprisals against Great Britain for restricting Japan's textile imports. The resultant active buying of fine crossbreds for Japanese mills was largely responsible for the sharp increase in prices in the last fortnight which makes the wool market the only bright spot in the Argentine economic picture.

headline.main: JAPANESE BUYING ARGENTINE WOOL; Activity, Resulting From Re- prisals Against Britain, Aids the Price Structure. GRAIN MARKETS ARE WEAK Export Demand Sluggish, and Disposal of Coming Harvest Is Uncertain.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 6. -- After weeks of indecision, hingeing upon the Cuban situation, Secretary Hull recommended to President Roosevelt today that Jefferson Caffery, Assistant Secretary of State in charge of Latin-American affairs, be sent as a delegate to the forthcoming Pan American conference at Montevideo.
